Add CTest support fixtures for exercising libcwd initialization across dependent and dlopen-loaded shared objects before any DWARF/location rewrite: create four tiny shared libraries under ctest/support named location_libtest1.so, location_libtest2.so, location_plugin1.so, and location_plugin2.so, with libtest1 privately depending on libtest2, runtime dlopen coverage for plugin1 from the libraries and plugin2 from a test executable, and global constructors/destructors in every library that explicitly initialize libcwd and print load/unload messages through dc::bfd. The fixture should capture and assert normal dc::bfd output, but when LIBCWD_PRINT_LOADING is set it should leave output on stderr for manual diagnostics, while normal CTest explicitly unsets that variable; also fix initialization so LIBCWD_PRINT_LOADING combined with LIBCWD_NO_STARTUP_MSGS does not restore uninitialized channel state. This fixture must only verify shared-object loading and libcwd initialization/logging behavior, not symbol or file:line lookup.
